article:
Skull and Bones, a secret society at Yale University, was founded in 1832. Until
1971, the organization published annual membership rosters, which were kept at
Yale's library. In this list of notable Bonesmen, the number in parentheses
represents the cohort year of Skull and Bones, as well as their graduation year.

There are no official rosters published after 1982 and membership for later
years is speculative. Some news organizations refer to them as a power
elite.
